text: Outi Aunula-Ylä-Sulkava (b. October 1992) is a Finnish long track speed skater. She was active between 1985 and 2000. Aunula-Ylä-Sulkava represented her nation three time as at the World All round Speed Skating Championships for Women. in 1992, in 1993 and in 1998. She participated at the European Speed Skating Championships for Women in 1993, 1994, 1995, 1996, 1997, and 1999. She also competed at other international competitions, including at ISU Speed Skating World Cups. == References == Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:Finnish sportspeople Category:Speed skaters
